<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/576.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Guatemalan Minister</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Guatemala</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 51.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Sir: I have the honor to advise you that, in accordance with the
                            convention concluded at Washington, December 20, 1907, the International
                            Central American Bureau was solemnly inaugurated yesterday at Guatemala
                            City.</p>
                        <p>I beg you to be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Luis Toledo
                            Herrarte.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>